\begin_layout Standard
Used to describe the potential field generated by some density distribution,
 the Poisson equation generalizes the Laplace's equation with:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{alignedat}{4} & \quad & \frac{\partial^{2}}{\partial x_{1}^{2}}u+\frac{\partial^{2}}{\partial x_{2}^{2}}u & = & \;- & f & \qquad\\
\Longrightarrow &  & -\nabla^{2}u & = &  & f
\end{alignedat}
\]

\end_inset

This thesis provides the following two datasets for the Poisson equation.
\end_layout

